# Animations in React with <div>Framer Motion</div> + TypeScript

Animations aren't just decoration they guide users, provide feedback, and make interfaces feel alive. But janky animations do the opposite.

Framer Motion + TypeScript = smooth, type-safe animations.

---

## Why Framer Motion?

```bash
npm install framer-motion
```

Simple API, powerful features, and excellent TypeScript support out of the box.

---

## Basic Animations with Type Inference

```typescript
import { motion } from 'framer-motion';

// motion.div, motion.button, etc. - all typed like native elements
const FadeInBox = () => {
  return (
    <motion.div
      initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }}
      animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
      exit={{ opacity: 0, y: -20 }}
      transition={{ duration: 0.5 }}
      className="p-4 bg-blue-500 text-white rounded"
    >
      I animate smoothly
    </motion.div>
  );
};
