## Which One Should You Choose?

| Pattern         | Best For                          | Complexity |
| --------------- | --------------------------------- | ---------- |
| useReducer      | Local component state             | Low        |
| Context + Hooks | App-wide simple state             | Medium     |
| Zustand         | Medium-large apps                 | Low        |
| Redux Toolkit   | Very large teams                  | High       |
| XState          | Complex flows (checkout, wizards) | High       |

---

## Key Takeaways

1. **Discriminated unions** make reducers bulletproof
2. **Custom context hooks** prevent runtime errors
3. **Zustand** offers Redux power with minimal boilerplate
4. **Selectors** prevent unnecessary re-renders

Start with useReducer for local state, reach for Zustand when things grow, and keep Context for simple theme/auth needs.
